cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.SI

The paper describes a family of probabilistic architectures designed for online learning, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. However, the focus on learning and the use of data conditioning make it most likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of neural networks, which could place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the mention of euclidean space and the potential application to computer vision suggest that it could also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the use of probabilistic architectures and the mention of convergence make it possible that it could belong to the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
